obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (26784)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263&sectionId=26784&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (including High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Madhya Pradesh shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to the`
  line `territory, which as from that day are the territories of Chhattisgarh State, stand transferred to the`
  line `corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer of the State of Chhattisgarh.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court of Madhya Pradesh and the decision of that High Court shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `(3) In this Section—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in the State of Chhattisgarh means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have laid if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in the State of Chhattisgarh, as`
  line `may be determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State or the Central`
  line `Government, as the case may be, or before the appointed day by the Government of the existing`
  line `State of Madhya Pradesh to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (26785)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263&sectionId=26785&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the existing State of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those`
  line `courts, notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts`
  line `has been transferred to the State of Chhattisgarh.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (26786)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263&sectionId=26786&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `The provision of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything in consistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (26787)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263&sectionId=26787&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00037_200028_1517807323263
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not in consistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
